      <hedline>
        <hl1>Breach at Los Alamos: Who'll Take the Blame?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Alan Rivers letter on loss or theft of two computer hard drives at Los Alamos National Laboratory as latest example of Clinton administration's 'shocking' disdain for national security (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The loss or theft of two computer hard drives containing highly sensitive data at Los Alamos National Laboratory (front page, June 13) is another shocking example of the Clinton-Gore administration's disdain for national security.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The loss or theft of two computer hard drives containing highly sensitive data at Los Alamos National Laboratory (front page, June 13) is another shocking example of the Clinton-Gore administration's disdain for national security.</p>
        <p>This latest in a series of security breaches is just added proof that  our commander in chief does not take these issues seriously. A high official must be held responsible for this breakdown in protection of our national defense secrets.</p>
        <p>ALAN RIVERS  Carmel, Ind., June 13, 2000</p>
      </block>
